On American Business Women's Day, the United States celebrates women in the workforce and those who have started their own businesses. The nation recognizes and honors their success and pledges to create an environment where women can excel in any field. Women are key to the success stories in every sector of the economy, breaking barriers and creating jobs. They are the fastest growing group of entrepreneurs in the country, owning over 40% of all businesses. These women-owned businesses are estimated to contribute $1.8 trillion in revenues in 2018. The administration is committed to supporting women in the workplace, with policies such as tax cuts, job creation, increased funding to women-owned businesses, and a national paid family leave program. The article calls on Congress to pass the program to help women succeed in the workforce and provide for their families.